Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Production date: 131 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 142.)
Curator's comments: Name Nikasagoras. Trimmed. From same die as 1925,0119.279 and Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0174.03.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0906)
